content:
Allow End Users to Download a Transcript of a Messaging Session

This article applies to: Messaging for In-App and Messaging for Web channels.

An Admin must enable the download transcript feature:

From Setup, enter Messaging Settings, and select Messaging Settings.
Click the downward arrow to the right of your channel, and select Edit.
Select Let customers download their conversation transcripts.
Save your changes.

End users can download a transcript by clicking the Menu icon, then selecting Request Chat Transcript. A transcript can contain up to 200 conversation entries and includes all time stamps in the GMT time zone. Languages not supported include Arabic, Hebrew, Amharic, and others. Unsupported characters are replaced with "?", and emojis display in greyscale or text.
title: Service Cloud Messaging Transcript Download
